%N A394048 The product of the smallest primes in every congruence class modulo n which are relatively prime to n.
%H A394048 Steven Lu, <a href="/A394048/b394048.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..576</a>
%e A394048 For n = 24, the congruence classes are 1, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19, 23, whose corresponding smallest primes are 73, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19, 23. Then a(24) = 73 * 5 * 7 * 11 * 13 * 17 * 19 * 23 = 2714296585.
%t A394048 Table[Times @@
%t A394048   Table[NestWhile[# + n &, r, Not[PrimeQ[#]] &], {r,
%t A394048     Select[Range[n - 1], GCD[n, #] == 1 &]}], {n, 24}]
%K A394048 nonn,new
%O A394048 1,2
%A A394048 _Steven Lu_, Mar 08 2026
